
CTRL/C

Cancels a command when typed during command entry.

Cancels command execution when typed twice during  command  execution.
(The first ^C does not echo.)

Halts a program and returns to TOPS-20 command level.  Generally, type
two  CTRL/Cs  to  halt a program that is executing; type one CTRL/C to
stop a program that is waiting for input.
